# HTML Files Rules

## Core Principles
- **Semantic Markup**: Use appropriate HTML5 tags
- **SEO Optimized**: Meta tags, Open Graph, Schema.org
- **Performance**: Preload critical resources
- **Accessibility**: ARIA labels, alt texts, semantic structure

## SEO Essentials
- **Title**: Descriptive, unique, 50-60 chars
- **Description**: Compelling, 150-160 chars
- **Keywords**: Relevant, comma-separated
- **Canonical**: Specify canonical URL
- **Robots**: Control indexing (index, follow)

## Social Media Tags
- **Open Graph**: Facebook, LinkedIn (og:*)
- **Twitter Card**: Twitter-specific (twitter:*)
- **Telegram**: Channel link (telegram:channel)

## Performance
- Preload critical fonts: `<link rel="preload" as="font">`
- Defer non-critical scripts
- Use modern image formats (WebP, AVIF)
- Minimize inline styles/scripts

## Accessibility
- Set `lang` attribute on `<html>`
- Use semantic tags: `<header>`, `<nav>`, `<main>`, `<footer>`
- Include ARIA labels for dynamic content
- Ensure proper heading hierarchy (h1 â†’ h6)

## Anti-Patterns
- Don't put business logic in HTML
- Avoid inline styles (use CSS/Tailwind)
- Don't duplicate meta tags
- Avoid excessive DOM nesting in root
